"Street Fighter" Live-Action Film Unveils Star-Studded Cast

The highly anticipated live-action adaptation of the beloved "Street Fighter" franchise has officially unveiled its full cast, and the lineup promises a fresh and dynamic take on the iconic characters. With a mix of Hollywood heavyweights, rising stars, and unexpected choices, the film is poised to deliver a bold new vision for the legendary fighting game series.

The ensemble bringing the World Warriors to life includes:

\* Jason Momoa as Blanka

\* Andrew Koji as Ryu

\* Noah Centineo as Ken Masters

\* Callina Liang as Chun-Li

\* Roman Reigns as Akuma

\* Cody Rhodes as Guile

\* 50 Cent as Balrog

\* Orville Peck as Vega

\* David Dastmalchian as M. Bison

\* Vidyut Jammwal as Dhalsim

\* Hirooki Goto as E. Honda

\* Andrew Schulz as Dan Hibiki

\* Olivier Richters as Zangief

\* Rayna Vallandingham as Juli

\* Alexander Volkanovski as Joe

\* Mel Jarnson as Cammy

\* Eric Andre as Don Sauvage

